  "findings": {
    "head_ready": "MTP head depth-1 in-top-8 = 1.0 (target next-token always in top-8); top-1 = 0.75-0.82; depth-1 rescuable (rank 2..8) = 0.18-0.25.",
    "tree_depth_starved": "At the MTP chain budget cap of 5 the balanced breadth-first tree trades depth for breadth: chain reaches depth 3 (hist {0:3,1:2,2:4,3:3}), widening to k>=3 caps at depth 2 (hist {1:8,2:5}) and LOSES net acceptance (alpha 0.277 vs chain 0.317). The 23% depth-1 branch-rescue does not pay back the sacrificed depth-2/3 chain agreement.",
    "gate_recovers_depth": "Only the confidence-gated narrow tree (k=2, thr=0.7) beats the chain: alpha 0.364 vs 0.317, visible 2.82 vs 2.58 tok/cycle. The gate falls back to the deeper chain on low-confidence cycles (6/11), restoring depth-3 acceptance while keeping depth-1 breadth on confident cycles.",
    "not_a_tok_s_win": "Per (B+1)/C_B ceiling and the #98 dispatch floor (verify fixed 711 + 240/row launches), even alpha=0.364 / 2.82 visible-tok-per-cycle does NOT beat AR until #98->#105/#101 land. This is the realizable-acceptance datum + tree-path validation, a necessary co-requisite, not a speedup."
